[Main]
Name=CENTER
Type=Constant
Header Files=dialogs.h, menus.h
Definition=#define CENTER (-1)

[Description]
A constant to describe a centered position for dialogs.

[Explanation]
When used in the <A HREF="$$LINK(DialogDo)">DialogDo</A> or <A HREF="$$LINK(menus.h/PopupDo)">PopupDo</A> command as a parameter, CENTER means
"center the dialog or popup menu on the screen in x, y or both directions," depending on which parameter
CENTER is used as.
